(See Dict. Ant. ‘ Cineia Lex.') ‘ Prag- matici ' were persons who helped the advo- cates with legal information in court. The name was taken from the Greeks, who em- ployed that sort of practitioner : ‘ apud Graecos infimi homines mercedula adducti ministros se praebent in judiciis oratori- bus,’ as Cicero says (De Or. 1. 45). See also Quintilian (Inst. xii. 3). The Romans did not hold them in much estimation.
